para_trans: the post of Registrar in the University
Department of Skills, Employment, Entrepreneurship and Innovation
Madam Cama Marg, Martyrdom Rajguru Chowk,

Number: - CAVIO: -2022 / Q. 09/2022 Entrepreneurship. Ratan Tata Ratan Tata Maharashtra State Skill University Act, 2021 (State Skill Mahasabha of 2021) In exercise of the powers conferred by section 14, sub-section (2) of the University Act, 2021, the Government of Maharashtra hereby appoints the Registrar to the office of the Registrar in the Schedule appended to this Act.
Specifying qualifications and experience for the purpose.
table_trans: A) Minimum 55% marks in the Master's degree examination of any statutory university or its equivalent in Category B of the 7 point standard of the University Grants Commission. B) Relaxation - I) Condition of minimum 55% marks prescribed in the Master's degree examination is relaxed by 5% for candidates who are already working in the university system. II) Candidates belonging to Scheduled Castes / Scheduled Tribes and Other Backward Classes may be exempted by 5% from the condition of minimum 55% marks prescribed in the Master's degree examination and the limit shall be 50. III) Minimum 55% prescribed in the Master's degree examination for candidates who have held a PhD degree before 19th September, 1991.

para_trans: This Government Order is available on the website of the Government of Maharashtra www.maharashtra.gov.in.
table_trans: A relaxation of 5% may be granted in the condition and the limit shall be 50%. c) Experience: 1) Experience as an Advocate (Senior Grade) with at least 15 years teaching experience / 8 years experience as a Lecturer or Associate Professor with a revised pay scale and academic administration as per UGC standards. Or 2) Comparative experience in research establishment and / or other institutions of higher education. Or 3) Administrative experience of 15 years out of which 8 years as Deputy Registrar or equivalent. d) Must have good knowledge of computers. d) Must have good knowledge of Marathi language. f) Must be proficient in English language communication skills.

1) Optimum qualification / experience in the field of management / law / engineering. 2) Experience in application of technology in administrative / legal / financial / establishment matters. 3) Administrative competence should be proved in an institution preferably in the field of research or higher education.
